<br>
On friday we picked fire pets all around and rolled through the warrens into stonebrunt.  We saw the kobolds, but decide exploring first would be a &quot;good&quot; idea.<br>
<br>
Our first memorable kill was a highland graniteback, followed by a kejek tiger (both red to entire group, group level was 18-20).  We sucessfully killed both by chain-casting and healing fire pets.  These fights (and the oddly weak exp) convinced us to head back to kobold killing.  The camp(s) to the right of zone were sufficient for the group to stay busy, and I don't think we'd have had any deaths if some of the party hadn't decided they wanted to work on Bind wounds...  low HP aggro is hard to shake sometimes.<br>
<br>
The evening wrapped up early with an encumbered walk back to erudin (even with 3-4 summoned bags and junking silver and copper).  The loot was more than acceptable, and the exp was ok.  We've had an in-group suggestion that once we all hit 20 we head back to Luclin and try Netherbian Lair.  Will likely be ready for that by next weekend at the latest.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the suggestion on research, but asking a high lvl magician to do combines for 5 players could get excessive.  We'll try to keep it in group and see how it goes...  <br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugekkobear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gekkobear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(8/21/02 6:31:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Aug 20th update</span><hr size=1> Ok, short day cause we have to work tomorrow, but we got together for 2 hours of killin.<br>
<br>
Target was Netherbian lair.  (we tend to target zones, just easier that way)<br>
<br>
At entry we had 2 lvl 20 and 3 lvl 19, all the 19's had lvl 20 spells on hand.  Set up 5 fire pets, too a few fungiod for exp/practice and started pulling.<br>
<br>
Early on we got a Trog King, with 2 or 3 adds (I think 3, but wasn't counting).  No deaths, no pet deaths (but close).  With that done we knew we could stay.  Also we got 2 more lvl 20's soon after.<br>
<br>
With some odd pathing we chose to move into the tunnels.  We had recently been buffed by high level players stopped by the odd sight of 5 gnome magicians all in lime-green.  As puller I don't think I stopped for more that an occasional pet heal the entire run.  I watched very few fights,  just sent in my pet and went looking for the next target.  <br>
<br>
All 5 of us gained over 4 yellow bubbles of exp in our 2 hours of playing, and a good time was had by all.  Loot was acceptable, with decent cash/words as well as 2 soiled breechclouts and some weaponry (spears and hammers).<br>
<br>
Considering that many of the pulls were yellow and/or red and quite a few were multiple I think we can safely say the &quot;pet squad&quot; theory is well proven up to and including lvl 20. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you have the opportunity to get some friends together and try this yourselves, I must say I haven't been disappointed yet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
